## ğŸ¯ **Your Goal**

â¡ Ensure that when your **file upload form triggers a full POST**, the selected sponsor + email type (and any other critical state) is **preserved** so the page doesn't reset dropdowns or other fields.

---

## ğŸ” **Why Hidden Fields Are the Right Solution**

â¡ The file upload form is isolated â†’ its POST does not include the main form's state (like selected sponsor/email type).
â¡ Adding **hidden fields inside the upload form** binds those values so they're submitted alongside the file.

â¡ This ensures:
âœ… Your managed bean retains the correct state
âœ… The view renders with correct selections after the upload POST

